This paper is primarily focused on the design and implementation of a system for detecting anomalous link quality degradation in wireless sensor networks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses various techniques developed to address challenges inherent in applying the threshold-based decision approach, which involves statistical analysis and decision theory. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the dynamic environment changes and the need for the network to react accordingly, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
